Finance Data-Analysis Portfolio — third-party data NOTICE
=========================================================

This repository's CODE is MIT-licensed (see LICENSE). The DATA it references
and ingests belongs to the respective providers and is used here under their
public/educational terms. Data snapshots committed under data/ are pinned,
hashed copies for reproducibility — NOT redistributed as an authoritative
source. Always re-fetch from the provider for current data.

Providers used across the portfolio (see docs/DATASETS.md):

- Aswath Damodaran (NYU Stern) industry datasets — https://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~adamodar/
  Free for educational/research use. Files are overwritten each January; this
  repo pins the Jan-2026 (TTM through ~Q3 2025) vintage with SHA-256 manifests.
  Attribution: data by Prof. Aswath Damodaran, NYU Stern School of Business.

- SEC EDGAR (data.sec.gov) — public domain U.S. government data; requires a
  descriptive User-Agent header per SEC fair-access policy.

- FRED (Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis), BEA, BLS, U.S. Census, NSF NCSES,
  Our World in Data, Oxford OxCGRT, NVD/NIST, CISA — public-sector or openly
  licensed sources; attributed per their terms.

- yfinance / Yahoo Finance, Stack Overflow Developer Survey (ODbL), Kaggle
  community datasets, Wikipedia (CC BY-SA) — used under their respective terms.

No proprietary/paywalled data (Statista, Macrotrends, Gartner/Canalys/Synergy,
GICS) is redistributed here.
